<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,325,1250]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Crown ochraceous with one spot on either side of median line in posterior half, most part of anterior marginal spot, black. Anterior half of pronotum black, posterior half ochraceous. Mesonotum black. Face and body beneath black. Legs mostly pale ochraceous. Forewing ochraceous, broad longitudinal fascia in clavus, similar fascia commencing from disc of forewing at about 0.33 from base and not reaching apex and apical area black; costal margin, narrowly black.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,325,1250]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Head narrower than pronotum. Crown, face and pronotum polished. Transverse impressed line on pronotum shallow.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,325,1250]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis box="[199,371,577,602]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Male genitalia</emphasis>
. Male pygofer height greater than length in lateral view, dorsal margin convex, apical membranous lobe finger-like, ventral pygofer process slightly exceeding length of lobe and gradually narrowed distally to pointed apex. Subgenital pale slightly narrowed distally with hair-like and macrosetae. Style elongate, with foot-shaped apophysis, toe prolonged into long process. Connective with stem slightly longer than arms. Aedeagus stout, dorsolateral lobes smaller and shorter than their process, latter quadrangular and in lateral view reaching ventral margin of aedeagal shaft, ventral margin of aedeagus with angular prominences, extension of atrium well developed and longer; in ventral view shaft and processes of dorsolateral lobes of similar length, shaft with lateral lobe-like projection, gonopore apical.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,325,1250]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis box="[199,392,865,890]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Female genitalia</emphasis>
. Seventh sternite with median conical lobe on posterior margin, with posterolateral angles rounded.
</paragraph>
